This paper is primarily focused on semantic image segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs), which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of boundary detection to improve segmentation accuracy, which is a technique that falls under the umbrella of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of ensemble classifiers, which is a common technique in graph theory (cs.GR). Finally, the paper deals with remote sensing data, which is a common application area for multimedia (cs.MM) research.
